Global Commercial Fleet Services Market Insights
Commercial Fleet Services Market size was valued at USD 68 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 109 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Commercial Fleet Services Market Overview
The global Commercial Fleet Services market size was valued at USD 215.8 billion in 2024 and is projected to grow at a CAGR of 6.3% from 2025 to 2030. The growing demand for efficient fleet management and technological advancements in fleet telematics and data analytics are driving market growth. Fleet services include vehicle leasing, fleet management, maintenance, and fuel management solutions. Companies are increasingly adopting fleet management services to improve vehicle uptime, reduce operating costs, and enhance overall productivity. The market is highly competitive, with the presence of both global and regional service providers offering comprehensive solutions for businesses of all sizes.

